value.value: This gene plays a role in transcriptional initiation.

A subtest of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures categorical, abstract reasoning. Students are asked to look at rows of pictured objects and indicate (by pointing) the single picture from each row that shares a characteristic in common with the single picture(s) from the other row(s).

A Working Memory subtest of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures visual working memory. The child views a stimulus page of one or more pictures for a specified time and then selects the picture(s) (in sequential order, if possible) from options on a response page.

A subtest of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures verbal concept formation and reasoning. Children are asked to describe how two words are alike or similar. This requires abstract verbal reasoning, auditory comprehension, and expressive language skills.
This gene is involved in the dephosphorylation of phosphatidylinositol 3-phosphate and phosphatidylinositol 3,5-bisphosphate.

A Visual Spatial subtest of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures the ability to analyze and synthesize information. Within a specified time limit, the child views a completed puzzle and selects three response options that, when combined, reconstruct the puzzle.
A composite score of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures a child's ability to problem solve with unfamiliar information or while navigating new situations.
A composite score of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures a child's speed and accuracy of visual identification, decision-making and decision implementation.
A composite score of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures a child's ability to access and apply acquired word knowledge.

Human MTMR2 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q21 and is approximately 104 kb in length. This allele, which encodes myotubularin-related protein 2, plays a role in dephosphorylation of phosphatidylinositol phosphates. Mutation of the gene is associated with Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease type 4B1.

A composite score of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures a child's ability to evaluate visual details and understand visual spatial relationships in order to construct geometric designs from a model.
CD40 ligand (261 aa, ~29 kDa) is encoded by the human CD40LG gene. This protein is involved in both binding to CD40 and the modulation of B-cell function.
A composite score of the Wechsler Intelligence Scale for Children that measures a child's ability to register, maintain, and manipulate visual and auditory information in conscious awareness.
Myotubularin-related protein 2 (643 aa, ~73 kDa) is encoded by the human MTMR2 gene. This protein is involved in the dephosphorylation of lipids containing phosphoinositol.
A regimen consisting of intraperitoneal (IP) carboplatin, intravenous (IV) paclitaxel, and IP paclitaxel that may be used for the treatment of ovarian, fallopian tube, and primary peritoneal cancers.
A regimen consisting of fluorouracil and paclitaxel that may be used in the treatment of esophageal and esophagogastric junction, and gastric cancers.

An indication that extracellular vesicles expressing PSMA (PSMA-EVs) were found at high concentrations in a sample. High levels of PSMA-EVs are seen in samples from subjects with malignant urologic cancers, including metastatic renal cell carcinoma (RCC), metastatic prostate cancer, and castration-resistant prostate cancer.

An indication that extracellular vesicles expressing PSMA (PSMA-EVs) were found at low concentrations in a sample. Low levels of PSMA-EVs are seen in samples from subjects with non-metastatic urologic neoplasms.
Bladder urothelial carcinoma confined to the lining of the bladder.
A stage term that refers to cervical carcinoma stages IA, IB, and IIA.
A protein encoded by the human CUX1 gene.

label.value: Early Stage Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A stage term referring to clear cell renal cell carcinoma that presents as a small tumor and is confined to the kidney.

label.value: Tumor Necrosis Factor Ligand Superfamily Member 6

value.value: Tumor necrosis factor ligand superfamily member 6 (281 aa, ~31 kDa) is encoded by the human FASLG gene. This protein plays a role in the positive regulation of apoptosis.
A stage term referring to colorectal carcinoma that is limited to the colon/rectum or local lymph nodes, without metastasis to distant anatomic sites.
A physician with specialized training in the diagnosis and treatment of musculoskeletal disease.
An orthopedist with additional training/certification in adult reconstructive surgery.
An orthopedist with additional training/certification in foot and ankle surgery.
An orthopedist with additional training/certification in trauma surgery.
A stage term referring to endometrial carcinoma that is confined to the uterus.
An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in pediatric otolaryngology.
An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in sleep medicine.
A stage term referring to esophageal carcinoma that is confined to the esophageal mucosa or submucosa.

label.value: Otolaryngology Plastic Surgery within the Head and Neck

value.value: An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in plastic surgery within the head and neck.
An ozonide of Terpene designed to oxidize tumor cells and control metastasis. (NCI)
Lymphotoxin-beta (244 aa, ~25 kDa) is encoded by the human LTB gene. This protein is involved in cell-cell signaling and immune responses.
A curated classification and nomenclature for the organisms in the public sequence databases that the National Center for Biotechnology Information (NCBI) maintains.

A stage term referring to hepatocellular carcinoma that presents as a single tumor with the largest diameter measuring 2 cm or less. The liver function is well-preserved and there is no vascular invasion or metastasis. (Barcelona Liver Cancer Classification).
An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in diagnosis and treatment of otolaryngologic allergy.

label.value: Early Stage Lung Non-Small Cell Carcinoma

value.value: A stage term that refers to lung non-small cell carcinoma stages I, II, and IIIA.
An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in diagnosis and treatment of otology and neurotology.
An otolaryngologist with additional training/certification in facial plastic surgery.
A stage term that refers to a malignant tumor confined to a limited area of the skin without lymph node or distant metastases.
Cervical carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.

label.value: Resectable Clear Cell Renal Cell Carcinoma

value.value: Clear cell renal cell carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.
This gene plays a role in transcriptional initiation and has testis-specific expression.
Endometrial carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.
Esophageal carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.

An orally bioavailable inhibitor of nuclear enzyme poly(ADP-ribose) polymerase (PARP) 1, with potential antineoplastic activity. Upon oral administration, PARP1 inhibitor IMP1734 selectively binds to and blocks the activity of PARP1, thereby preventing the repair of damaged DNA via the base excision repair (BER) pathway. This enhances the accumulation of DNA strand breaks and promotes genomic instability eventually leading to apoptosis. PARP1 catalyzes post-translational ADP-ribosylation of nuclear proteins that signal and recruit other proteins to repair damaged DNA and plays a key role in the repair of single strand DNA (ssDNA) breaks and double-strand breaks (DSBs).
Malignant solid neoplasm that is amenable to surgical resection.
Triple-negative breast carcinoma that is amenable to surgical resection.
